##Autopsy of the first and second cases of new coronary pneumonia completed, why is it so important?

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

"Pathological diagnosis is the gold standard for disease diagnosis. "

At 3:50 am on February 16, the autopsy of the country's first patient with new coronavirus pneumonia was successfully completed by Tongji Medical College professor of Forensic Pathology Liu Liang and his team at Golden Pool Hospital in Wuhan, fourteen hours later, they completed a second autopsy.

So far, two autopsies have been sent to reveal the new coronavirus pathogenesis, pathological features and their clinical relevance, the highly anticipated report is expected to be published in 10 days.

"The results of the first autopsy of the lung have been available, and we can see changes in the exudation and deterioration of the lung, but more data are needed to make a comprehensive judgement of the pathological conditions, " Ding Yanqing, a Chinese pathologist and professor of Southern Medical University, told China Newsweek, his team performed the world's first autopsy on a SARS patient in 2003 during the fight against SARS.

"We are still working and need to concentrate, " Liu Liang said in an interview with the Health Times shortly before 10 a.m. on Thursday, writing on his personal media account, "no interviews or interruptions. " The dissection on February 16 was mainly based on material, "The virus has to be inactivated, so the tissue has to be soaked a little bit more. Then the sections are put under a microscope to see what changes have taken place in the cell structure and the tissue structure. " Liu Liang says further microscopic, pathological and virological studies are needed.

Two Cadavers were dissected over 18 hours

At 9 p.m. on Feb. 15, waiting for a reply, Liu Liang received a phone call from Zhang Dingyu, the Director of Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital. "We have one for the autopsy, " Liu Liang later recalled, "The national, provincial and municipal health committees break the rules, take action first, and then write official documents. ".

The day before, Liu Liang on a personal media platform, "call for the rapid development of new pneumonia death of individual autopsy" , 15 am, Liu Liang received the National Health and Health Commission Medical Administration response, he was invited to attend a conference on the autopsy of a new case of pneumonia, when he "optimistically estimated that the autopsy would take 2-3 days to land. ".

The call came sooner than expected, and Liu Liang rushed a team from every corner of Wuhan to the hospital. In the meantime, a vacuum cleaner operating room has been set aside to ensure that the virus does not spread while being dissected.

"thanks to the consent of the family, we observed a moment of silence before the autopsy was conducted so quickly, " Liu Liang wrote.

Both patients were from the Shanghai Medical Team's ward. The first shanghai-hubei medical team was one of the provincial teams that first arrived in Wuhan. They were opposite each other in support of the Jinyintan Hospital. The medical team leader and deputy director of the Shanghai First People's Hospital, Zheng Junhua, introduced that, even with the use of artificial liver, artificial kidney, ECMO and other state-of-the-art methods, there are still a number of patients with difficulties in rescue, unfortunately died, understanding the pathogenesis of first-line treatment is crucial to the emergence of autopsy reports.

After the death of the first patient, Zheng's team after more than two hours of communication, the family in understanding the significance of the anatomical pain signed consent. Out of concern for the privacy of the deceased and their families, Zheng said only that the two deceased patients were over 55.

Wearing a breathless suit, Liu Liang's team waited until just after 1 a.m. , and at 3:50 a.m. , the first autopsy was completed.

"Now I know what a Hazmat suit can do. Put on less than 10 minutes, full sweat, the result in dry peacetime can easily dry work, sweat, breathing difficulties, eyewear goggles hazy. Like altitude sickness, the first case is more than half done, there is a flustered dizziness hypoglycemia performance. On the one hand, it means you're old. But really appreciate the hard work and dedication of the medical staff. Must pay tribute to all the ordinary first-line medical fighters!"Liu Liang wrote on his personal media platform.

After the first autopsy, Liu Liang went home to rest for more than two hours, and immediately summarized and reported to the team what could be improved in the autopsy process. At about 11 a.m. on the 16th, Liu Liang again received a notice from Zhang Dingyu, the director of Jinyintan Hospital. "there is another case that needs an autopsy. " The emergency team members rushed to the hospital again. The autopsy started at 4 p.m. that day and ended at 6:30 p.m, "soaking wet, " Liu Liang felt cold and went home to isolate himself again and record his 18-hour workday.

Pathological diagnosis is the gold standard of disease diagnosis

Liu Liang's call came the same day that 63,946 cases had been confirmed nationwide, including 1,382 deaths. Compared with SARS in 2003, the clinical manifestations of severe NCP were more advanced, some patients suffered from severe hypoxia and serious heart injury, but there was no systematic anatomical and pathological examination of the dead individuals.

"If we want to treat these patients, we need to know more about the pathogenesis and the physical condition of the patients, " Hu Ming, director of the ICU at Wuhan Lung Hospital, told China News Weekly. "We need basic research to keep up. That is, autopsy and pathology reports. ".

After the outbreak of SARS in 2003, the pathogen was initially considered as "chlamydia" with little damage, but the patients were seriously ill and had a high mortality rate. After the autopsy of the first SARS patient, Ding Yanqing, a professor of pathology at the Southern Medical University, combined with the results of four autopsies conducted at the time at the Southern Hospital, concluded that the pathogen should be "virus" , this provides an important scientific basis for the treatment of SARS.

"Pathological diagnosis is the gold standard for disease diagnosis, " Ding told China News. The pathology community has been calling for "case autopsies" in wechat friend circles since around the Spring Festival. On Jan. 29, Bian Xiuwu, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and Director of the Institute of Pathology at the Covid-19, issued a proposal to the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention on conducting autopsy work on death cases from infectious diseases, on the same day, the National Health Commission reported 7,711 confirmed cases and 170 deaths.

There are many problems in the clinical treatment of npv pneumonia that have not been scientifically explained. Why is upper respiratory virus far less positive than lower respiratory tract? How does the "ground-glass" pathology of the patient's lungs compare with other viral pneumonia? What are the reasons and mechanisms for the rapid progression of late disease?

"regarding the rapid progress of the disease and the serious heart damage in the later stage, I have discussed with Bian Xiuwu academician that, with reference to the pathological results of SARS, it may be caused by a cytokine storm, " Ding explained, in 2003, he first proposed in the British "Journal of Pathology" that "lung and immune organs are the main target organs of SARS virus attack" , and then published in 2006, "SARS Pathogenesis Research" , it is suggested that the over-expression of proinflammatory factors is closely related to acute lung injury and multiple organ damage caused by SARS, which is now called "cytokine storm" . When tissue cells are damaged, the body produces an overactive immune response, producing large amounts of cytokines that cause the cells of the body's tissues to denature, necrosis, Vascular permeability, and extravasation of blood and plasma.

A cytokine storm also triggers a massive release of Nitric Oxide, further diluting the blood and damaging blood vessels, lowering blood pressure, leading to tissue Hypoxia, low blood pressure, multiple organ dysfunction and Disseminated intravascular coagulation.

"these need a certain number of autopsy pathology studies, Comprehensive Analysis. " Ding Yanqing said that unlike the onset of SARS, this new coronavirus pneumonia has a long incubation period and mild early symptoms, requiring the selection of cases with different conditions, for example, deaths from sudden exacerbations after a period of treatment may provide a more comprehensive picture of the overall situation.

Bian Xiuwu, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, has set up a "tent-like" autopsy room at the Central War Zone Hospital to meet Biosafety Level III standards in preparation for the autopsy of the new type of coronary pneumonia, according to Ding. "The lack of an autopsy room for the Class A infectious disease in our country is a pressing issue now, and we don't know what the new coronavirus will face after that, but we need to be prepared, " Ding said, "At least one province should have a biosafety-protected Class III BSL-3 Autopsy Laboratory. "
